---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
// NOTE: detailed baseline aligned with the HLB Ireland and FutureRange
// policies — have it reviewed by the group's legal adviser before launch.
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Mentora Group"
  description="How Mentora Group collects, uses, shares and protects personal data, the legal bases we rely on, how long we keep data, and the rights you have under the GDPR."
>
  <section class="page-hero on-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="lede">Last updated: July 2026</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          Mentora Group ("we", "us") is the holding company of HLB Ireland, an
          audit, accounting and tax advisory firm, and FutureRange, an IT
          services firm. Our registered address is The Courtyard, Carmanhall
          Road, Sandyford, Dublin 18, D18 NW62.
        </p>
        <p>
          Mentora Group is the data controller for personal data collected
          through this website. We process personal data in accordance with
          the General Data Protection Regulation (EU 2016/679) ("GDPR") and
          the Irish Data Protection Act 2018.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Scope of this policy</h2>
        <p>
          This policy covers this website and general enquiries made to the
          group. When one of the group's firms provides services to you — for
          example audit, accounting, tax, payroll, outsourcing, managed IT or
          cybersecurity services — the engagement is governed by that firm's
          own privacy policy and engagement terms:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://www.hlb.ie/privacy-policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">HLB Ireland privacy policy</a> — which also covers matters specific to regulated professional services, such as anti-money-laundering identification, engagement files and payroll processing;</li>
          <li><a href="https://futurerange.ie/privacy-policy-2/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">FutureRange privacy policy</a> — which covers data processed in the delivery of IT and security services.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. What personal data we collect</h2>
        <h3>Data you give us</h3>
        <p>
          When you contact us by form, email or phone, we receive the details
          you choose to share: your name, email address, phone number,
          company, the area you are interested in, and the content of your
          message. If you apply to work with us, we receive the information in
          your application. Providing this information is voluntary, though we
          cannot respond to an enquiry without contact details.
        </p>
        <h3>Data collected automatically</h3>
        <p>
          Like most websites, our hosting provider records limited technical
          data in server log files: IP address, browser type and version,
          operating system, referring pages, and the date and time of visits.
          We use this data in aggregate to keep the site secure and working;
          we do not use it to identify individual visitors.
        </p>
        <h3>Data from the firms</h3>
        <p>
          Where you are already a client or contact of HLB Ireland or
          FutureRange, the relevant firm may share your business contact
          details within the group so the right team can deal with your
          enquiry.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Why we use it and our legal bases</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Responding to enquiries and managing business relationships</strong> — our legitimate interest in dealing with the people who contact us and in administering and promoting the group's business.</li>
          <li><strong>Providing services</strong> — where processing is necessary for a contract with you or to take steps at your request before entering one.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal and regulatory obligations</strong> — including company law, tax law and the anti-money-laundering obligations that apply to the group's regulated services.</li>
          <li><strong>Consent</strong> — where we rely on consent (for example optional marketing communications), you may withdraw it at any time, without affecting processing already carried out.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do not use personal data for automated decision-making or
          profiling that produces legal or similarly significant effects.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          This website does not use advertising, analytics or tracking
          cookies. Only cookies that are strictly necessary for the site to
          function may be set. You can block or delete cookies through your
          browser settings at any time without affecting your use of this
          site. If we introduce analytics in future, this policy and our
          cookie controls will be updated first.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Who we share it with</h2>
        <p>We do not sell personal data. It may be shared with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Group companies</strong> — HLB Ireland and FutureRange, so the right team can answer you;</li>
          <li><strong>Service providers</strong> — the IT and cloud providers that host our website, email and systems, acting under GDPR-compliant data-processing agreements;</li>
          <li><strong>Professional advisers and auditors</strong> — where necessary for the running of the group;</li>
          <li><strong>Regulators and authorities</strong> — including the Revenue Commissioners, the Companies Registration Office, the Data Protection Commission or others, where the law requires or permits it.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. International transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Our systems are hosted principally within the European Economic
          Area. Where a service provider processes data outside the EEA, we
          rely on an adequacy decision of the European Commission or
          appropriate safeguards such as the EU Standard Contractual Clauses.
        </p>

        <h2>8. How long we keep it</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Enquiries</strong> — retained as long as needed to handle your enquiry and any business relationship that follows from it;</li>
          <li><strong>Client engagement files</strong> — generally retained for six years after the engagement ends, per the firms' policies and professional obligations;</li>
          <li><strong>Anti-money-laundering records</strong> — retained for five years after the business relationship ends, as the law requires;</li>
          <li><strong>Unsuccessful job applications</strong> — retained for up to twelve months unless you agree to a longer period;</li>
          <li><strong>Server logs</strong> — retained for a short period for security purposes and then deleted.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>9. How we protect it</h2>
        <p>
          We apply appropriate technical and organisational measures,
          including encryption in transit, access controls limiting data to
          the people who need it, and staff training. If a personal data
          breach occurs that we are required to notify, we will notify the
          Data Protection Commission without undue delay and where feasible
          within 72 hours, and — where the breach is likely to result in a
          high risk to you — we will tell you directly.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Your rights</h2>
        <p>Under the GDPR you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Access</strong> — request a copy of the personal data we hold about you;</li>
          <li><strong>Rectification</strong> — have inaccurate data corrected and incomplete data completed;</li>
          <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — have your data deleted where there is no lawful reason for us to keep it;</li>
          <li><strong>Restriction</strong> — limit how we use your data while a question about it is resolved;</li>
          <li><strong>Objection</strong> — object to processing based on legitimate interests, and to direct marketing at any time;</li>
          <li><strong>Portability</strong> — receive the data you provided to us in a structured, machine-readable format;</li>
          <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> — at any time, where consent is the basis of processing.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, contact
          <a href="mailto:info@hlb.ie">info@hlb.ie</a> or phone
          +353 (0)1 291 5265. We respond within one month, extendable by two
          further months for complex requests, in which case we will tell you.
          We may need to verify your identity before acting on a request.
        </p>
        <p>
          You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the supervisory
          authority: the <strong>Data Protection Commission</strong>,
          6 Pembroke Row, Dublin 2, D02 X963 — phone +353 1 765 0100 —
          <a href="https://www.dataprotection.ie" rel="noopener">dataprotection.ie</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Children</h2>
        <p>
          This website and the group's services are directed at businesses and
          their advisers, not at children. We do not knowingly collect
          personal data from anyone under 16; if we become aware that we hold
          such data, we will delete it.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Links to other websites</h2>
        <p>
          This site links to other websites, including those of HLB Ireland
          and FutureRange. This policy applies only to this website — check
          the privacy policy of any site you visit.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. The version published
          on this page, with its "last updated" date, is the one that applies.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal { padding: 80px 0 110px; }
</style>
